---
import PageLayout from '../../layouts/PageLayout.astro';
import FIRECalculatorBase from '../../components/calculator/FIRECalculatorBase.astro';
---

<PageLayout
  title="Barista FIRE Calculator — Plan Your Semi-Retirement with Part-Time Work"
  description="Free Barista FIRE calculator for hybrid early retirement. Calculate your FIRE number based on part-time income and expenses. Work part-time, let investments cover the rest."
  canonical="https://truefinancetools.com/barista-fire-calculator"
  ogImage="https://truefinancetools.com/og-barista-fire-calculator.png"
  ogImageAlt="Barista FIRE Calculator - Semi-Retirement with Part-Time Work"
  pageType="article"
  keywords="barista fire calculator, barista fire number, semi-retirement calculator, part-time retirement, fire calculator part-time, barista fire strategy"
>
    <FIRECalculatorBase fireType="barista" />

    <section class="border-t border-hairline bg-canvas-soft py-16">
      <div class="mx-auto max-w-4xl px-4 sm:px-6">
        <h2 class="mb-8 text-center text-2xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-ink" style="letter-spacing: -0.02em;">
          What is Barista FIRE?
        </h2>

        <div class="prose prose-gray max-w-none text-body">
          <p class="mb-4">
            <strong>Barista FIRE</strong> is a hybrid approach to early retirement where you save enough to cover most expenses, then supplement your income with part-time work. The name comes from the idea of working as a barista — a low-stress job that often provides health insurance benefits.
          </p>

          <p class="mb-4">
            Unlike traditional FIRE, where your investments must cover 100% of expenses, Barista FIRE acknowledges that many people enjoy some work but want freedom from the 9-5 grind. Your investments cover the gap between your expenses and your part-time income.
          </p>

          <h3 class="mb-3 text-lg font-semibold text-ink">The Barista FIRE Formula</h3>
          <div class="rounded-lg bg-canvas-soft-2 p-4 font-mono text-sm text-ink">
            FIRE Number = (Annual Expenses − Part-Time Annual Income) × 25
          </div>

          <p class="mb-4">
            For example, if you spend $50,000 per year and earn $20,000 per year part-time: ($50,000 − $20,000) × 25 = $750,000. That's $500,000 less than traditional FIRE — a significant difference that can shave years off your savings timeline.
          </p>

          <h3 class="mb-3 text-lg font-semibold text-ink">Who Should Choose Barista FIRE?</h3>
          <div class="grid gap-4 sm:grid-cols-2">
            <div class="rounded-lg border border-hairline bg-canvas p-4">
              <h4 class="mb-2 text-sm font-semibold text-ink">Health Insurance Seekers</h4>
              <p class="text-sm text-body">Those who need employer-sponsored health insurance but want to escape full-time work.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="rounded-lg border border-hairline bg-canvas p-4">
              <h4 class="mb-2 text-sm font-semibold text-ink">Social Connectors</h4>
              <p class="text-sm text-body">People who enjoy social interaction and structure that part-time work provides.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="rounded-lg border border-hairline bg-canvas p-4">
              <h4 class="mb-2 text-sm font-semibold text-ink">Passion Projectors</h4>
              <p class="text-sm text-body">Those who want to pursue passion projects while maintaining some income.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="rounded-lg border border-hairline bg-canvas p-4">
              <h4 class="mb-2 text-sm font-semibold text-ink">Bridge Builders</h4>
              <p class="text-sm text-body">People using part-time work as a bridge between full-time work and full retirement.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="border-t border-hairline bg-canvas py-16">
      <div class="mx-auto max-w-4xl px-4 text-center sm:px-6">
        <h2 class="mb-4 text-2xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-ink" style="letter-spacing: -0.02em;">
          Explore Other FIRE Strategies
        </h2>
        <p class="mb-8 text-body">Compare different approaches to find the right one for your lifestyle.</p>

        <div class="grid gap-4 sm:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3">
          <a href="/lean-fire-calculator" class="group rounded-lg border border-hairline bg-canvas p-5 text-left shadow-sm transition-all hover:shadow-md">
            <h3 class="mb-2 text-sm font-semibold text-ink group-hover:text-link">Lean FIRE Calculator</h3>
            <p class="text-xs text-body">Minimalist approach with lower expenses.</p>
          </a>
          <a href="/fat-fire-calculator" class="group rounded-lg border border-hairline bg-canvas p-5 text-left shadow-sm transition-all hover:shadow-md">
            <h3 class="mb-2 text-sm font-semibold text-ink group-hover:text-link">Fat FIRE Calculator</h3>
            <p class="text-xs text-body">For those who want a luxury retirement lifestyle.</p>
          </a>
          <a href="/coast-fire-calculator" class="group rounded-lg border border-hairline bg-canvas p-5 text-left shadow-sm transition-all hover:shadow-md">
            <h3 class="mb-2 text-sm font-semibold text-ink group-hover:text-link">Coast FIRE Calculator</h3>
            <p class="text-xs text-body">Let compound interest do the heavy lifting.</p>
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
</PageLayout>
